<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 07 at 3:38AM EST  by NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly</headline>
<description>...INCREASING SNOW INTENSITY EARLY THIS MORNING...
As of 330 AM, doppler radar indicated snow increasing in intensity
across much of the area. There will be areas of moderate to heavy
snow occurring with rates reaching 1 to 2 inches per hour. This
will result in untreated roads becoming snow covered and
hazardous. In addition, the visibility will significantly be reduced
to one half of a mile or less at times. If you must travel early
this morning, allow extra time and adjust your driving speed for
the winter conditions.</description>
